Refrain from using government vehicles other than in the conduct of official business;

In transporting patients, recommended practices must be observed to ensure that the patient will be transferred without tissue injury, physical and emotional discomfort. As much as possible, the vehicle to be used has complete healthcare facilities to give comfort and aid for the safety of the patient;

Establish and enforce suitable penalties against employees who use, or authorize the use of government vehicle for unofficial purposes or other than the performance of government transactions; and

Strict compliance with the above Circular is enjoined to ensure the effective conservation and proper utilization of government motor transportation.

Strict implementation of the provisions of COA Circular No. 97-002 shall be observed.  Likewise, the following internal control measures may be adopted by the LGU in order to further reduce the unliquidated balance of the cash advances, viz:
Cash advances shall only be granted to officers and employees with no outstanding balance;
Proceeds from the reimbursement of travelling expenses in any form for officials and employees with outstanding balance shall first be applied to his/her obligations;
All cash advances and reimbursements should be accompanied by a certification from the Municipal Accountant to the effect that the claimant has no outstanding cash advance balance and
Require the accountable officer to sign an authority to deduct their outstanding cash advances from their salaries or emoluments due them until full settlement of their obligations.

