Strict compliance with the above Circular is enjoined to ensure the effective conservation and proper utilization of government motor transportation.

Strictly abide the basic requirements before granting cash advance to officers and employees. Adherence to relevant laws, rules and regulations must be properly observed; 

Designate properly bonded Disbursing Officer whose function is to perform disbursing of government funds for municipal transactions. Cash advances for the government programs/activities must be granted only to eligible officers and employees; and

Require the Accountable Officer to submit properly and completely accomplished Report of Disbursements in accordance with Annex 46 of NGAS Volume II thru the Municipal Accountant. Liquidations with incomplete supporting documents must be returned to the AO to comply the deficiency/ies before crediting the AO’s cash advance.
